  "Convert rights declarations into a workable licensing market instead of a binary open/closed web.": "Guculani imimemetelo yemalungelo ibe imakethe yelayisensi lesebentako esikhundleni sewebhu lelinani lelilodwa levulekile/lelivaliwe.",
  "Copied ✓": "Kucoshiwe ✓",
  "Copy": "Kopisha",
  "Correct positioning: independent research drafts, protocol proposals, and an open specification experiment.": "Kubekwa lokufanele: tidrafti tecwaningo letitimele, tiphakamiso teliphrothokholi, kanye nelutshalo lwencazelo levulekile.",
  "Corrected an earlier default: Belgium (BE) now maps to Dutch instead of French — Flemish speakers are the country’s majority (~60%) over Walloon French speakers (~40%).": "Kulungisiwe simiso sangaphambilini: iBelgium (BE) nyalo ihlotjaniswa nesiDutch esikhundleni sesiFulentji — bantfu labakhuluma siFlemish bayincenye lenkhulu yeve (~60%) kunalabakhuluma siFulentji seWalloon (~40%).",
  "Corrected an earlier default: Kazakhstan (KZ) now maps to Kazakh instead of Russian, now that a Kazakh translation exists — the same kind of fix as the earlier Belgium correction.": "Kulungisiwe simiso sangaphambilini: iKazakhstan (KZ) nyalo ihlotjaniswa nesiKazakh esikhundleni sesiRussia, njengobe nyalo kunesihumusho sesiKazakh — luhlobo lokufanako lekulungiswa njengekulungiswa kwaseBelgium kwangaphambilini.",
  "Could AI Be Conscious?": "Could AI Be Conscious?",
  "Crawler access rules": "Imitsetfo yekufinyelela kwesikhrola",
  "Crawler simulator": "Sibonelo sekutikhrola",
  "Currency": "Imali",
  "Custom tier": "Libanga lelitakuliwe",
  "Daily Nous reports on a retracted Journal of Medical Ethics submission containing multiple fabricated, AI-hallucinated references — complete with fake university affiliations and defunct email addresses — that the author reportedly left uncorrected even after being given a chance to fix proofs. The piece contrasts this with Bioethics, whose automated reference-checking would have caught the problem, and argues the real bottleneck isn't detection technology (one commenter's script flagged the fake citations in under a minute) but unpaid reviewer labor and publishing incentives that reward throughput over scrutiny.": "I-Daily Nous ibika ngesitfombiso lesahoxiswa se-Journal of Medical Ethics lesasinemitfombo leminyenti lengakalungi, lekhicitwe yi-AI ngekunganembi — lecinisiwe netinhlangano tenyuvesi tebucili kanye netikhala te-imeyili letingasasebenti — lokwatiwa kutsi umbhali wakushiya kungakalungiswa ngisho nasekunikwe litfuba lekulungisa emaphrofu. Lesitfombiso sisibeka eceleni ne-Bioethics, lekuhlolwa kwayo kwemitfombo ngekutiphindzaphindza bekutakuyibamba lenkinga, futsi liphika kutsi inkinga yangempela akusiwo buchwepheshe bekutfola (skripthi yalomunye umphawuli yabamba tinkomba tekucaphuna letingakalungi ngaphansi kwemzuzu lolodwa) kepha ngumsebenti wababuki bemitfombo longabhadalwa kanye netikhutsato tekushicilela letivuza kunyenti kwemsebenti kunekuhlolisisa.",
  "Data free-riding vs. trillion-dollar AI valuations": "Kutfola imininingwane mahhala kunetilinganiso te-AI letifika kuma-thriliyoni emadola",
  "DeepMind CEO calls for an independent standards body to regulate frontier AI": "DeepMind CEO calls for an independent standards body to regulate frontier AI",
  "Demis Hassabis proposed a FINRA-style regulator for frontier model releases: labs would submit models for review up to 30 days before deployment, voluntary at first, with a path toward mandatory compliance in the US market.": "Demis Hassabis uphakamise sikhulumi sekulawula lesifana ne-FINRA setikhicito temodeli lesekugcile: emalabhorethri atawuveta emamodeli ekuhlolwa emalanga langu-30 ngaphambi kwekusetjentiswa, ngekutitjala kucala, nendlela leya ekuhambisaneni ngekuphocelela emakethenini iase-US.",
  "Denied": "Kwaliwe",
  "Deployable policy starter template": "Sifanekiso sekucala setimtsetfo lesingasetjentiswa",
  "Deployable policy starter template at /downloads/agiright-policy-starter.zip — a minimal static site with the full machine-readable layer, ready for Cloudflare Pages or any static host.": "Sifanekiso sekucala setimtsetfo lesingasetjentiswa ku-/downloads/agiright-policy-starter.zip — sayithi lesincane lesimile lesinelohlaka lolugcwele lolufundzeka ngemishini, lesilungele i-Cloudflare Pages nobe nayiphi indzawo lemile yekusinga.",
  "Deploying machine-readable policies on your site": "Kufaka imitsetfo lefundzeka ngemishini kusayithi lakho",
  "Disclaimer": "Sicwayiso",
  "Distinct from human UI, SEO, or plain APIs, the AI Ingestion & Capability Layer gives websites a machine-facing architecture: a Manifest Layer (entry points like /llms.txt and /ai/manifest.json), a Corpus Layer (machine-readable knowledge), a Capability Layer (agent-callable tools), and a Governance Layer (provenance, licensing, versioning). Static-first, upgradeable toward APIs and MCP. Note: in this paper AICL names the ingestion architecture; on this site's protocol pages AICL refers to the AI Content Licensing Layer.": "Kuhlukile kusayithi le-UI yemuntfu, i-SEO, nobe ema-API lalula, i-AI Ingestion & Capability Layer inika ema-website luhlaka lolubhekene nemishini: Luhlaka Lwemanifesti (tindzawo tekungena njenge-/llms.txt kanye ne-/ai/manifest.json), Luhlaka Lwe-Khophasi (lwati lolufundzeka ngemishini), Luhlaka Lwebuciko (emathulusi lashaywa ngema-ejenti), kanye neLuhlaka Lwebulawulo (imvelaphi, kunikwa kwelayisensi, kubekwa kwemavesheni). Lumile kucala, lungakhushulwa kuye ema-API kanye ne-MCP. Catsi: kuleliphepha i-AICL yisho luhlaka lwekungena; emakhasini eliphrothokholi alesisayithi i-AICL ibhekisela Ku-Luhlaka Lwekunikwa Kwelayisensi Kwelokucuketfwe Kwe-AI.",
  "Do Large Language Models Possess a Theory of Mind? A Comparative Evaluation Using the Strange Stories Paradigm": "Do Large Language Models Possess a Theory of Mind? A Comparative Evaluation Using the Strange Stories Paradigm",
  "Docs": "Ticukumbisa",
