  "Validate": "Cinisekisa",
  "Validator": "Validator",
  "Verified dataset markets and collective licensing": "Imakethe temininingwane lecinisekisiwe kanye nekunikwa kwelayisensi ngekuhlangana",
  "Verified in both LTR and RTL contexts: the panel mirrors correctly for Arabic and Persian without any special-casing, using logical CSS positioning.": "Kucinisekisiwe etimeni letimbili LTR ne-RTL: ipaneli iyalayathi ngendlela lelungile yesiArabhu nesiPheshiya ngale kwekutsintfa kwesento lesikhetsekile, isebentisa kubekwa kwendzawo nge-logical CSS.",
  "Verify": "Cinisekisa",
  "Version history of this site and its protocol drafts.": "Umlandvo wemavesheni walesisayithi kanye netidrafti tayo teliphrothokholi.",
  "Version history of this site and its protocol drafts. Breaking spec changes are recorded here.": "Umlandvo wemavesheni walesisayithi kanye netidrafti tayo teliphrothokholi. Kuguculwa lokwephulako kwencazelo kubhalwe lapha.",
  "Versioned specifications, JSON Schemas, and the policy files actually deployed on this site. Every file can be downloaded, validated, and cited directly.": "Tincazelo letinemavesheni, Tikimu te-JSON, kanye netifayela temtsetfo letifakwe ngempela kulesisayithi. Ifayela ngalinye lingalayishwa, licinisekiswe, futsi licaphunwe ngalokucondzile.",
  "Versioning": "Kubekwa Kwemavesheni",
  "Versions": "Emavesheni",
  "Video and audio companions to the protocols and papers — the AI rights layer, watchable and listenable.": "Imithombo yemidvwebo nemsindvo lehambisana netiphrothokholi kanye nemaphepha — luhlaka lwemalungelo e-AI, lolungabukwa futsi lulaleleke.",
  "Videos": "Imidvwebo",
  "Want to generate your own policy file?": "Ufuna kukhicita ifayela lakho lemtsetfo?",
  "Web fonts are loaded from Google Fonts, which receives standard font requests from your browser. No other third-party scripts are used.": "Emafonti ewebhu alayishwa ku-Google Fonts, lekutfola ticelo letijwayelekile tefonti kusuka ebhrawuza yakho. Akukho letinye tiskripthi tenhlangano yesitsatfu letisetjentiswako.",
  "What AI systems may do with content: read, summarize, transform, retrieve, train, commercialize, redistribute. The AICR ruleset and the AICL licensing layer make these rights declarable and transactable.": "Loko tinhlelo te-AI letingakwenta ngelokucuketfwe: kufundza, kufingqa, kuguculwa, kutfola, kufundzisa, kwenta ngekwekuhweba, kusakata kabusha. Luhlu lwemitsetfo ye-AICR kanye neluhlaka lwekunikwa kwelayisensi lwe-AICL kwenta laamalungelo amenyetelwe futsi asebente ngekuguculwa.",
  "What a server can return when an AI crawler requests licensed content without a license token — a machine-actionable quote instead of a dead end.": "Loko sesitfulo singabuyisa nasikhrola se-AI sicela lokucuketfwe lokunelayisensi ngale kwethokheni yelayisensi — intengo lesebenta ngemishini esikhundleni sendzawo lengenandlela.",
  "What this site is": "Lesisayithi siyini",
  "What this site is not": "Lesisayithi asisiko yini",
  "When The Machines Deserve Our Consideration": "When The Machines Deserve Our Consideration",
  "Whether AI may learn, to what depth, for which purposes, and under what obligations. Being read is not being learned from; \"not prohibited\" is not \"learnable\". AIRS and AILP turn learning permission into a graduated, machine-readable spectrum.": "Ingabe i-AI ingafundza, ngabu-nzulu-bani, ngato yiphi tinhloso, kanye nangaphansi kwaluphi tibopho. Kufundzwa akusiko kufundzelwa; \"akuvinjelwe\" akusiko \"kungafundzeleka\". I-AIRS kanye ne-AILP tiguca imvumo yekufundza ibe luhlu loluhlukanisiwe, lolufundzeka ngemishini.",
  "Whitepapers": "Tincwadzi Letimhlophe",
  "Whitepapers & Docs": "Tincwadzi Letimhlophe & Ticukumbisa",
  "Whitepapers remain English-first by design; machine-readable files stay language-neutral.": "Tincwadzi letimhlophe tisala tisebentisa siNgisi kucala ngekwakheka; tifayela letifundzeka ngemishini tisala tingakhetsi lulwimi.",
  "Who is behind it": "Ngubani losemuva kwako",
  "Why AI Needs Minimum Ethical Protections": "Why AI Needs Minimum Ethical Protections",
  "Why AI might not gain moral standing: Lessons from animal ethics": "Why AI might not gain moral standing: Lessons from animal ethics",
  "Why a single allow/deny bit cannot govern AI-era content use — and what a rights layer looks like instead.": "Kungani linani lelilodwa lelivumelekile/lelaliwe lingakwati kulawula kusetjentiswa kwelokucuketfwe kwesikhatsi se-AI — futsi luhlaka lwemalungelo lubukeka njani esikhundleni saloko.",
  "Why undefined openness gets cleaned out of training pipelines": "Kungani kuvuleka lokungachaziwe kuhlanjululwa etindleleni tekufundzisa",
  "Wilks, Ladak, and Loughnan (University of Edinburgh) argue that philosophical debate over AI consciousness overlooks psychological research on animal ethics — the same cognitive and social biases that limit moral consideration for animals will likely limit it for AI too, regardless of whether AI ever becomes conscious.": "Wilks, Ladak, kanye no-Loughnan (University of Edinburgh) baphika kutsi imphikiswano yefilosofi mayelana nebuciko besimo semtimba be-AI ayikanaki lucwaningo lwengcondvo mayelana netimiso tetilwane — tiyinso letifanako tekuciphuka kanye netemphakatsi letikhawulela kucatjangelwa kwemtsetfo tetilwane kungenteka tikhawulele nakuye ku-AI, kungakhatsateki kutsi ingabe i-AI ingaba nebuciko besimo semtimba yini.",
  "You are leaving AGIRight.org": "Uyashiya i-AGIRight.org",
