  "rag_use — retrieval-augmented generation, retention windows": "rag_use — khicito lokusekelwe kutfolo, emawindi ekugcinwa",
  "read_access — whether AI may fetch and read the content": "read_access — ngabe i-AI ingatfola futsi ifundze lokucuketfwe",
  "redistribution — republishing or redistributing content or derivatives": "kusakatwa kabusha — kushicilela kabusha nobe kusakata kabusha lokucuketfwe nobe imikhicito lesuka kuko",
  "research pages & whitepapers": "emakhasi ecwaningo & tincwadzi letimhlophe",
  "robots.txt and llms.txt govern access and visibility, not learning depth or use permissions. AIRS proposes expressing AI rights as a proportional, use-specific spectrum across ten dimensions — access, indexing, inference input, embedding, training, fine-tuning, distillation, memory, output, attribution/compensation. AILP translates this into /ai/rights-spectrum.json, letting creators declare granular permissions with compensation models ranging from free through license-required to revenue share.": "I-robots.txt kanye ne-llms.txt kulawula kufinyelela nekubonakala, hhayi bunzulu bekufundza nobe imvumo yekusetjentiswa. I-AIRS iphakamisa kukhulunywa ngemalungelo e-AI njengeluhlu lolulinganako, lelikhetsekile ngekwesisetjentiswa, kuti tigaba letilishumi — kufinyelela, kubekwa ngendzawo, kungeniswa kwekwesekela, i-embedding, kufundzisa, kulungisa lokucophelela, kucindzetela, inkhumbulo, umphumela, kubongwa kwemtfombo/inkhokhelo. I-AILP ihumusha loku ibe ku-/ai/rights-spectrum.json, ivumela badali kutsi bamemetele imvumo lehlukanisiwe ngemamodeli enkhokhelo kusuka kumahhala kuya ekudzingekeni kwelayisensi kuya ekwabelaneni ngenzuzo.",
